    <div class="service-content">
      <p>If you've never been through a home appraisal before — or it's been a few years — you might be wondering what actually happens during the process. Here's a clear, step-by-step overview of what to expect when a Las Vegas Appraisal Co. appraiser visits your property.</p>

      <h2>Step 1: Scheduling</h2>
      <p>After you contact us (by call, text, or our online form), we'll confirm the appointment within one business day. Most inspections are scheduled within 1–3 business days of your request. We're available six days a week, so we can usually work around your schedule.</p>

      <h2>Step 2: The Property Inspection (30–90 minutes)</h2>
      <p>The inspection is the appraiser's only visit to the property. During this time, the appraiser will:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Measure the exterior dimensions of the home (for square footage verification)</li>
        <li>Walk through every room, noting the layout, condition, and features</li>
        <li>Photograph the exterior, interior rooms, kitchen, bathrooms, and any notable features or deficiencies</li>
        <li>Note the lot size, garage, pool, outbuildings, and other improvements</li>
        <li>Assess the overall condition of the property</li>
      </ul>

      <p>You don't need to clean obsessively, but a tidy, well-maintained home makes a better impression. Make sure all areas are accessible — including the attic, crawl space, and garage — and that any permits for additions or renovations are available if asked.</p>

      <h2>Step 3: Market Research and Report Preparation</h2>
      <p>After the inspection, the appraiser returns to the office to analyze the data. This involves researching recent comparable sales ("comps") in your neighborhood, reviewing local market trends, and applying adjustments for differences between your property and the comparables. This research phase typically takes 1–2 days.</p>

      <h2>Step 4: Report Delivery</h2>
      <p>At Las Vegas Appraisal Co., every report passes a 6-point quality control review before it's sent to you. You'll receive a complete, professionally formatted appraisal report — usually within 2–3 business days of the inspection. The report includes the property description, photos, market analysis, comparable sales grid, and the appraiser's certified opinion of value.</p>

      <h2>A Few Tips to Prepare</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Have a list of any recent improvements or renovations handy (year completed and approximate cost)</li>
        <li>Ensure all utilities are on if the home is vacant</li>
        <li>Make sure pets are secured during the inspection</li>
        <li>Have HOA information available if applicable</li>
      </ul>

